specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: Finn Juhl, sofa model '57', fabric upholstery, steel, teak, leather, Denmark, design 1957. An extraordinary sofa designed by Finn Juhl. The sofa was exhibited for the very first time in the Tivoli Gardens in Copenhagen during 1957. The extravagant design is characterized by the armrests that look to resemble the spread-out wings of a bird. The beautiful two-tone fabric upholstery emphasizes the sculptural quality of the monumental design. Please note that this sofa is from a more recent production by One Collection in Denmark, now known as House of Finn Juhl. House of Finn Juhl is the licensed manufacturer of the designs of Finn Juhl. The sofa was exhibited in a boardroom for 20 years but hardly used. It is in immaculate condition. Marked with a signature and the early round medaillon label as pictured. Finn Juhl (1912-1989) was a Danish furniture designer and architect, best known for his innovative and expressive furniture designs. He was a pioneer of the Danish Modern movement, which emphasized simplicity, functionality, and the use of natural materials. Juhl's work is characterized by its sculptural forms, organic shapes, and use of vibrant colors. His most famous pieces include the Chieftain Chair and the 45 Chair. Juhl's designs have influenced generations of designers and continue to be celebrated for their timeless elegance and innovative spirit.

specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: Olivier SANTINI's "MW02" armchair is handcrafted in France.A numbered and signed piece. The sides are made of transparent glass, allowing it to blend seamlessly into any style of space. This subtle and airy armchair stands out as a modern and innovative work that will bring a harmonious touch to your environment. The transparent black TPU seat gives it a sophisticated character while ensuring unparalleled comfort and remarkable elegance. The translucent sides evoke a delicate weightlessness of the seat, which appears to navigate gracefully through space. Combining striking lightness with boldness, this armchair not only optimizes the furniture space but also infuses your space with a distinctive personality. A rare, unique piece, appealing to decorators and art enthusiasts in search of originality and exceptional pieces. The seating, crafted in black TPU, revolutionizes the furniture sector with its innovative design and unique aesthetics. It distinguishes itself through its durability. Olivier Santini was born in 1966. He has been drawing since childhood, prioritizing ideas and originality. During his student years, he developed a deep interest in aesthetics, graphic contours, and the properties of materials, while enjoying opportunities to interact and exchange ideas with art artisans. At the age of 20, he founded a group of marketing and design agencies, putting his experience and creativity at the service of clients, achieving immediate success. While analyzing furniture designs, he noticed a lack of variety, color, and uniqueness, leading him to create his own furniture collection. His goal was to create different, fun, and vibrant furniture with optimistic and refreshing colors that bring light and joy to both indoor and outdoor spaces. MIAW 2022 Design Award Winner.

Known for his innovative approach and versatility, Bellini has created iconic furniture pieces, architectural landmarks, and industrial designs that have left a profound impact on the world of design. His work often blends functionality with timeless aesthetics, incorporating cutting-edge technology and traditional craftsmanship. Bellini remains a revered figure in the realms of architecture and design, inspiring generations of creatives with his visionary creation

name: Minimal Style, Solid Wood Stool, Textiles or Leather Seatings, Caning Backboard

specifications.rawSpecificationsHTML: The Wing chair solid wood collection, flexibility, modern aesthetics, comfort and softness are the keywords for this collection. The concept is inspired by the B-52 plane design, this inspiration gave us the freedom to create a collection where the design appropriate subtle elements, harmonic transitions and thin but resistant wood thicknesses, that gave life to a unique and contemporary collection. Our studio objective was to abstract most of the figurative elements and arrive in the very sweet spot in this design, the “cream”, driving the details in a three dimensional way. All our objects are drawn using the Da Vinci's "golden section", and the wing collection is not an exception, this assures pleasing proportions and contrast between each design part that composes the object in a deep study in the thicknesses and the relationship between each component sizing. The Wing chairs and stools are crafted with passion using premium materials and the latest technologies in furniture manufacturing, with a very precise quality control, on its beauty there is the subtle variations between the wood veins in a real living item without ethnic appeal yet been warm resulting in well-rounded comfortable pieces, delicate in design and sturdy in construction. All this qualities converge in and merge in a collection made to participate in the life of our clients as a breeze, comfortably, pleasant, harmonic and positive. We offer a caning back solution and a solid back option, stools and chairs versions. There are three solid wood tonalities as standard and a solid Ebonized black, we also offer wood harmonization if needed, so we work the tonality to approximate a particular target. All woods and materials are certified and responsibly sourced and manufactured. Listing features the black ebonized solid wood stool with natural distress leather 20363, natural caning back. This piece seat height may be customized for your needs of counter height or bar height. The stool seating height is customizable in up to 29in (74cm) or bellow. *Our pieces are made with passion and attention to quality, comfort, and design, which are our priorities for daily users. We use ultra-premium materials that are carefully crafted through manual processes and solid wood sculpting. Please consider a tolerance of up to 2 inches in the dimensions, plus or minus. The seat height may impact the overall dimensions within this range, as we adjust from below.
